Assistant: To find the sum of all odd integers between $500$ and $700$, first calculate how many odd integers there are:
\[
\begin{align*}
\text{consecutive odd integers from } &: 501 - 500 + 1 \\
&= 2
\end{align*}
\]
And since the difference between consecutive odd integers is $2$, how many to the end of $701$ will consider:
\[
\begin{align*}
\text{consecutive odd integers up to } &: \frac{701-501}{2}+1
\end{align*}
\]
Therefor in total:
\[
\begin{align*}
S &= n/2*(a+(l-a)/d) \\
S &= \frac{701-501}{2}+1/2*2 \\
S &=\frac{200}{2} *2 \\
S &= \boxed{200}
\end{align*}
\]

